Product name: Essential Oils / ESSENTIAL OIL KIT - Travel - Pick 2 / For Acne / For Anxiety / For Sleep / For Headaches / For Allergies / For Aromatherapy
Description:
At Orglamix, our goal is to make aromatherapy easy! We offer an extensive selection of high quality essential oils and aromatherapy products for all ages and spaces.
Essential Oil Travel Kit Duo | Pick Two includes your choice of any two of the following essential oils. Each amber glass bottle contains 40-50 drops of pure, undiluted essential oil -- making them the perfect solution for having your favorite oils with you all the time.
Choose from:
• Eucalyptus (Eucalyptus radiate) Revitalizing, invigorating, clarifying. Eucalyptus essential oil is said to clear the head, soothe respiratory tract, boost immunity, and relieve congestion.  It acts as a stimulant and can ease mental fatigue. It is a considered to be excellent for treating colds and flu, muscular aches and pain and insect bites.
• Lemongrass (Cymbopogan flexuosus) Purifying, stimulating, cleansing.  Sweet, citrusy fragrance, balances emotions, relieves nerves and eases stress. Lemongrass essential oil can be used to treat large pores and as a scalp conditioner. It is a considered to be excellent for poor circulation, indigestion, to break a fever and as an insect repellent. 
• Lavender (Lavandula angustifolia)  Calming, soothing, normalizing, balancing. A universal oil with countless applications. Lavender essential oil balances and calms emotions. It’s useful for all skin types. Lavender is considered to be excellent for inflammation, insomnia and athlete’s foot.
• Lemon (Citrus limon)  Cleans, freshens, uplifting; clarifies thought. Lemon essential oil is sometimes referred to as "Liquid Sunshine".  It can be used to treat very oily skin.  It is a considered to be excellent for cellulite, colds, head lice.
• Lime (Citrus aurantifolia) Uplifting, refreshing, elating. The pleasant citrus aroma of lime may help mental clarity and encourage creativity. Today, lime essential oil is best known throughout the world as a way to help support a healthy immune system. It is a considered to be excellent for cleaning, uplifting moods and detoxifying.
• Peppermint (Mentha piperita) Revitalizing, invigorating, cooling. Soothes headaches, clears and sharpens the mind, can help to lose weight. Peppermint essential oil is said to help revive and boost a tired mind and calm nerves. It is a considered to be excellent for relieving nausea, easing headaches, treating colds and flus and soothing muscular pain. 
• Rosemary (Rosmarinus officinalis)  Purifying, uplifting. Rosemary has been revered by healers for centuries for its digestive uses and for muscle aches and pains.  It combats oily skin. Rosemary is said to stimulate the mind to combat mental exhaustion and fatigue. Rosemary essential oil is considered to be excellent for treating rheumatism, getting rid of head lice, stimulating circulation and reliving colds and flu.
• Tangerine (Citrus reticulata)  Purifying, cheerful, uplifting. Tangerine essential oil is said to treat cellulite, boost immunity, muscle fatigue, and morning sickness. It counteracts oily skin. It’s balancing and uplifting to the mind, and may help to relieve anxiety.
• Tea Tree (Melaleuca alternifolia) Cleansing, purifying, renewing.  One of the most powerful immune stimulant oils, and can be used to fight infections of all kinds.  It is also helpful in clearing blemishes and acne.  Tea Tree  essential oil is considered to be excellent for treating reliving althlete’s foot, plantar warts, cold sores, blemishes, acne, insect bites and colds and flu. 
• Wild Orange (Citrus sinensis) Uplifting, invigorating, disinfecting, immune-boosting. Orange essential oil is said to enhance concentration, help relieve stress and calm nerves. It also helps relieve oily skin.  It is a considered to be excellent for reducing and treating cellulite.
Safety Notes: For external use only. Do not use directly on skin, dilute in a carrier oil. Do not apply to broken or irritated skin. If skin sensitivity occurs, discontinue use. If you are pregnant, nursing or taking any medications, consult your doctor before use. Discontinue use and consult your doctor if any adverse reactions occur. Keep out of the reach of children. Keep oils away from eyes. Flammable.
---------------------------------------------------------------
SUGGESTED USEAGE
---------------------------------------------------------------
•Anti-aging face remedy:
-In a shallow bowl, mix half a tablespoon Almond Oil and one drop Lavender Oil. 
-Dip your fingers into the mixture, rub hands together, and let the natural heat from your body release the aromatic properties of each oil. 
-Begin application by gently pressing and sliding fingertips and palms on both sides of your nose, working your way up and out towards your hairline and down onto your neck and chest. 
Relaxing body massage:
-Using a bowl or mixing cup, blend one tablespoon Almond Oil, one drop Lavender Oil, and one drop Eucalyptus Oil. 
-Pour desired amount into the palm of your hands, then rub hands together and allow your natural body heat to help release the aromatic properties of each oil. 
-Massage gently onto skin as desired. 
Toning and firming body massage:
-Using a bowl or mixing cup, blend one tablespoon Almond Oil, one drop Lemongrass Oil, and one drop Peppermint Oil. 
-Pour desired amount into the palm of your hands, then rub hands together and allow your natural body heat to help release the aromatic properties of each oil. 
-Massage gently onto skin as desired. 
Aromatic bath:
-Add four to five drops of your preferred essential oil in a tub filled with water and stir well for an invigorating or relaxing effect. 
-If your skin is very sensitive, you can dilute the essential oil in a tablespoon of Almond Oil. 
Soothing foot bath:
-Add five drops of an essential oil of your choosing in a bowl of hot water or in an electric foot bath appliance and soak your feet for 15 minutes. 
Nourish and shine hair oil:
-In a shallow bowl, mix one tablespoon Almond Oil, depending on hair length and thickness, and two drops of an aromatic essential oil of your choosing. 
-Dip fingers into mixture and apply a small amount to the length and tips of hair as an aromatic leave-in treatment for healthy shine. 
-For a deeper treatment, apply a larger amount to length and leave on for 30 to 60 minutes, then rinse thoroughly. 
Refreshing mornings room aroma:
-In a diffuser, mix half a tablespoon water, four drops Peppermint Oil,  two drops Lemon Oil and two drops Lime Oil. 
-If you do not have a diffuser, you can use a bowl filled with one cup of hot water and double the amount of oil drops listed above. 
Peaceful nights room aroma:
-In a diffuser, mix half a tablespoon water, four drops Lavender Oil and two drops of Wild Orange  Oil. 
-If you do not have a diffuser, you can use a bowl filled with one cup of hot water and double the amount of oil drops listed above.
